    "updated_at": "2015-11-10T19:53:39Z",
    "body": "This is just how it is. Extern crate declarations really ought to be placed at the root. `use` statements are always absolute and we really can't change this -- both because of backwards compatibility, and because the name resolution algorithm itself becomes rather horribly complex otherwise. The reason is that when the root of your path depends on what's in scope, strange relationships arise between `pub use` and so forth.\n",
