    "created_at": "2015-11-11T18:43:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-11T18:43:04Z",
    "body": "I like the suggestion idea but (my-other-machine problem) I would say I vaguely remember a suggestion along those lines was emitted. It may have been, \"Hey try super or self.\"\n\nIf I'm prototyping a feature by just dumping it in the first convenient file, I don't want what I'm going to suggest to be on all the time but, if there was a way to lint a type or set of types for the work that you'll have to do to move them out to a module that might be a convenience. Not only the crate references but (an issue I excluded from the scope of this report) the `pub`'s I had to add once I had moved the code. \n\nMy above suggestion could help with a general rust compiler pattern: The compiler hardly ever tells me all that's wrong with my code if I am compiling it for the first time after an attempt to refactor it. \n",
